nu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kdumontnu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kdumontnu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kdumontnu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kdumontnu/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-05-27T13:34:57Z","updated_at":"2022-05-28T18:33:01Z","body":"Looks like the ability to watch a folder recursively was only [added in the latest](https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/commit/cee088b0db01076deb11c037fe8b64b238b005a2) Rust version. \r\n\r\nIâ€™ll give it a shot.\r\n\r\n**Update**: I tried using [`rerun-if-changed`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/build-scripts.html#build-scripts) from build scripts, but I could not get it to work like I wanted. It actually appears it's not intended to do what we're looking for. It seems `rerun-if-changed` is meant to tell cargo whether or not to (re)run the build script on build (vs using cached builds), NOT whether it should run watch the file/directory while running to rebuild. \r\n\r\nInstead, [`cargo-watch`](https://crates.io/crates/cargo-watch) seems to be the tool for this job. I have no idea if this is what Tauri is using to watch directories though. \r\n\r\nI apologize if I misunderstand something here, as I'm pretty new to Rust.\r\n\r\n> Our watcher has nothing to do with the build script. But we're not watching every package in a workspace, only tauri folders.\r\n\r\nMy goal with this feature request is to add the ability to customize files/directories in the tauri watcher and/or have tauri follow my local cargo dependencies by default.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tauri-apps/tauri/issues/comments/1139625650/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"kdumontn